The paper deals with the problem of Android malware detection using machine learning techniques, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed approach is based on eigenspace analysis, which is a common technique used in machine learning and pattern recognition (cs.AI). The paper also involves empirical evaluation of the proposed method, which falls under the category of experimental evaluation in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with the characterization of Android applications using static analysis, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper involves the use of features derived from static analysis, which is a common technique used in data science and machine learning (cs.DS).
